= The mothers and the highway

The Madres Veracruzanas — founded by thirty mothers from Xalapa the year Chernobyl's meaning landed — now hold the coast's attention every Saturday: the sit-ins, the marches to the plant gates, the coastal highway blocked by ranchers and fishing cooperatives in coordinated shifts. And the movement has done its electoral arithmetic in public: candidates will be measured against the reactor.

Cárdenas answers from the campaign: cancel Laguna Verde. The sentence detonates along the Gulf — the first time a presidential campaign has adopted a citizens' movement's demand whole.

[? if laguna = 1 : Your two years inside the coalition pay their dividend now: the coast's committees know your people by name, and the movement's electoral turn runs partly on rails you laid. ?]

- @al_seis: Weld the coast's movement to July: voter registration drives at the sit-ins, casilla training for the coalition's own people.

