The Saturday sit-in acquires a voter-registration table; the highway blockade schedule now avoids the casilla-training calendar, by coordination. A movement of mothers, ranchers and fishermen has decided the ballot is a blockade by other means — and on the sixth of July, the Gulf coast will count accordingly.
